      <Placemark>
        <name>USS Gerald R. Ford (CVN-78)</name>
        <styleUrl>#vessel</styleUrl>
        <description>Branch: USN&#xA;Status: transit — CVN-78 completed a record-breaking deployment in the Mediterranean Sea after transiting the Suez Canal from the Red Sea. Expected to return to Norfolk, Va., after breaking post-Cold War deployment records, signaling sustained naval pressure on Iranian-backed proxies in the Strait of Hormuz.&#xA;Type: Aircraft Carrier Strike Group&#xA;Source: ai_intel</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>2.6,36.8,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>USS Tripoli (LHA-7)</name>
        <styleUrl>#vessel</styleUrl>
        <description>Branch: USN&#xA;Status: deployed — America-class amphibious assault ship USS Tripoli operating in the Philippine Sea as part of disaggregated ARG operations. Conducted replenishment-at-sea with USS Rafael Peralta (DDG-115), demonstrating US Navy&#39;s ability to project power in the Western Pacific amid rising tensions with China.&#xA;Type: amphibious_ready_group&#xA;Source: ai_intel</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>134.8,12.4,0</coordinates>
